## Chunk 1 ‚Äî R1 factory + provenance tag (build first; Chunk 2 reads the tag)

### `make_entry(try_id, operation, parent, parents, status, result, **extra) -> dict`
Centralizes archive-entry construction. Called at ALL FOUR append exits of `run_one_try`
(MutationError after LLM call; general mutation exception; train/eval error; final
survived-evaluation append) ‚Äî locate them by those descriptions. **[MATCH]** the exact fields
each site currently sets (try_id, operation, parent_try_id, parent_try_ids, timing/cost fields,
result, status mirror) and reproduce them in the factory so behavior is identical; `**extra` (or
explicit params) covers per-site differences. Each exit keeps deciding WHEN to append; the
factory only builds WHAT.

Factory additionally sets the provenance tag on every entry (including failures):
- `origin`: the operation that produced this candidate (reuse the existing operation label).
- `born_try`: `try_id` (in scope at all sites).
- `lineage_id`, by inheritance rule:
  - `novelty` birth ‚Üí mint a fresh id (deterministic, e.g. `f"nov{try_id}"` ‚Äî no RNG needed).
  - `improve` / `repair` child ‚Üí parent's `lineage_id`.
  - `combine` child ‚Üí **rule (a)**: parse the existing comma-separated `parent_try_ids`, look up
    both parents in the archive; if either parent's lineage is novelty-originated (its
    `lineage_id` was minted by a novelty birth), inherit THAT id; else inherit the first
    parent's. Deterministic.
  - Seed/root entries (no parent) ‚Üí a root id (e.g. `"seed0"`).
  - **Backward-compat:** parents created before this change lack `lineage_id` ‚Äî treat missing as
    root/seed lineage (`entry.get("lineage_id", "seed0")`). Do not crash on old archives.

**Verification (Chunk 1):** run a short search; assert every row in tries.csv / archive has
`origin`, `born_try`, `lineage_id`; a novelty try mints a new id; its improve-children carry the
same id; a combine of (novelty-lineage √ó tree-lineage) inherits the novelty id. Confirm the four
exits produce byte-identical entries to before, plus the three new fields.

